cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GR, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with hierarchical partitions of trees and their visualization, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of these partitions for embedding ultrametrics into Euclidean space suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The aspect ratio of the partitions is a key concern, which is a topic in computational geometry and graph drawing (cs.GR). Finally, the use of these partitions for visualization suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of information visualization (cs.SI).
